caption: Ordered takeout on a Tuesday night. Food was delicious! I’m Pakistani so I was hoping to find good desi food outside of devon and this place was definitely it! I got the chicken khadi (the tastiest dish I got), nihari, special seekh kabob, naans, and kheer. Everything was yummy! I’m definitely going to go back to try their other dishes. For sure getting the khadi again! I didn’t find any of the dishes spicy so if you’re weary of heat this place is a save bet. The food has a modern twist so it’s not 100% traditional Indian but really yummy and I’d probably order from here before other indian/pakistani restaurants!
Most delicious and fresh Indian food I have had in while..Excellent customer services...

The Punjabi chef M.Singh did not disappoint.  The owner and staff were extremely friendly, and the food hit the spot!  The tamarind chutney was unique and flavorful.  Homestyle Punjabi dishes and of course my fav laccha paratha. Overall great desi spot!

Great food, great staff, and all around great experience. Food is properly spiceded which is rare outside of India.  Probably takes the spot of my favorite Indian restaurant outside of India. Food style reminded me of Dishoom in London.
Loved the eggplant bharta!
Soooooo delicious 😋. Really amazing lamb shank tahiri 🥰🍴🍗. Delishhhh

We were running errands and if course they ran longer than expected and I pulled up Yelp and said restaurants near me. This was the first result and it was AMAZING!  We had appetizers of samosas with homemade sauces. Main courses of Fish Basant with Jeera rice, Takka Tak with chicken and cauliflower rice, and Chicken Makhani with Basmati rice, and a side of Eggplant Bharta all served family style. Not pictured are desert of Kheer (rice pudding) and Gulab Jamun Cheesecake (lemon cheesecake). We also tried the Trumer Pils. Everything was so good and well done!  The staff was friendly, incredibly knowledgeable, and very welcoming. The restaurant interior was also very well done and appealing. Side note, I love their silverware too!  Will be going back and taking friends. I do recommend reservations while capacity rules are in place as they are taking all precautions.  Side note, I wasn't hungry upon going in, so this review isn't based on being starving!
Great reception and pretty tastier food in the midst of eye catching ambiance.
Best indian in the city hands down! Great flavor and some spice but it's lovely! Very nicely done interior. Highly recommend!

Wonderful dine in experience! Started out with the Jackfruit cutlet which paired beautifully with the mint chutney. Also the Chicken Malai Cilantro was super tender. The Seafood Khichdi was browned well on a bed of riced cauliflower and lentils. Spicy, but complimented the salmon.  The Malai Kofta was superb. Highly impressed with this new take on Indian. Very modern atmosphere and will be coming back very soon to try more items on the menu.

My new favorite Indian place in the city. From the appetizers, entrees and even the sides were delicious.  Their menu is tight and well organized.  Great flavors and attentive service. Crispy Samoas Yellow Dal Chana Masala Cilantro Chicken Seekh Kebobs Lamb Roganjosh Go here
So, so, so happy Basant is now in the neighborhood. Excellent food, very friendly service, and a really nice atmosphere. Already one of my favorite restaurants in area.
Wonderful people and food, everything perfectly spiced!

I happened to walk by a couple of days ago and noticed this new Indian restaurant in the neighborhood. Ordered takeout tonight and everything was delicious.  The samosas were perfectly flaky on the outside and moist on the inside. All the dishes were perfectly fresh and tasty. I can honestly say that this is among the top Indian restaurants I have dined at. I can’t speak to the ambience or service but it seemed nice inside. Very happy to see this addition.

My wife and I ordered take out from Basant last night and they very much exceeded our expectations.  We've had our fair share of Indian food throughout the years in the states and overseas and can confidently say Basant is right at the top in terms of overall flavor and quality.  We cannot wait to order again and eventually dine in person post pandemic.

We were excited to see Basant open in our neighborhood and finally tried takeout last night. My husband is half-Indian so we have high expectations, and this place absolutely blew us away! Can’t wait to order again!
Great new addition to the neighborhood, you can definitely taste the quality and freshness of their ingredients and dishes, looking forward to returning soon!

I’m down the street from this restaurant so when I saw this was opening I got so excited. Indian restaurants always skimp out on the rice but this place gives a whole lot! On top of that I got the Chicken Makhani and it was delicious. I’ll be returning.

I ended up here because I used to frequent this place when it was a pizzeria. I figured I would give it a try. I'm not in the city much and didn't want to drive around hungry. I became violently ill after eating their take out. I was sweating and shaking and vomiting in the washroom for 4 days.
Awesome food, friendly staff.  Definitely coming back for more!
Saw this resturant and wanted to try it out. Kadai chicken and butter chicken was amazing. Also the gulabjamun cheesecake is a must 😋

Really impressed and excited to have this new spot close by. We got several different items and I loved them all. The chutney was a nice surprise, will definitely order it again - kind of a more complex 'sweet and sour'/spicy flavor. I thought the spice level was great. The Yellow Dal and Chicken Tikka were delicious, as was the naan.

Did not really know what to expect being a brand new restaurant. My wife and I I agree that this food completely blew away our expectations, flavors and preparation perfection . If they keep up this quality we will have no problem going back on a regular basis. Very grateful to have such a good Indian restaurant in the neighborhood now. Five stars all around!!
Amazing food, great service, and an overall great experience. Every dish I've tried has been delicious, and the serving sizes usually let me enjoy leftovers!
very good indian! the yellow daal and the saag paneer in particular where to die for, the fact that they make it in house is so special

My friend ordered many of their dishes for an extravaganza of ‘culinary delights Friday night’!  Everything we tried was delicious and I’m a bit of a depressed take-out connoisseur due to the pandemic.  My favs:  jackfruit cutlet, salmon, eggplant, and butter chick.  My only not-love was the samosa, but considering samosas can be had almost anywhere, not a big deal!  Yay for a new restaurant opening up in tough times and a gorgeous interior to boot.
Delicious 😋😋😋😋😋 Gulab Jamin Cheesecake is genius! Salmon was extradionary! Flavorful dishes

I was excited when a new restaurant opened near me so I gave it a try tonight. What a great new restaurant!  The best Indian food I've had in a long time!  I chose 4 dishes and each were completely different from each other but totally harmonious! Clean, complex, fresh food.  AND they offer cauliflower rice which was perfect in place of regular rice.  Absolutely delicious and the service was so warm and friendly!

New restaurants opened during the pandemic need our support!  Just ordered delivery from Basant thru Uber Eats and it was quickly delivered, piping hot & fresh, and delicious!!  Tried the Chicken Basant, black dal, garlic Naan, samosas, chutney, and received a complementary jackfruit dish (that was awesome!!).  Fab flavor throughout, but not spicy (I didn't specify anything when ordering so now I know to ask for a bit more heat next time). There will definitely be a next time!

Ordered the lamb roganjosh with naan.  This dish was very creamy with a solid amount of spice.  Heat seekers will probably want to try a different dish, though.  I think it's a little bit pricey compared to the other couple area Indian restaurants and kind of wish there were smaller/cheaper portion sizes.  There's a lot of interesting dishes on the menu, so I think it's a great choice for groups who are willing to share.

Delicious food. Ordered pickup and staff were friendly and food was ready in good time. Food was flavourful, very tasty. I ordered the makhani with paneer and my husband ordered Takka tak with lamb. Both flavourful, but not particularly spicy hot - which is fine, we didn’t ask for that. Would definitely go again and try other items.
This is the best Indian food we have eaten in a long time!

This place is Awesome!  We had app -sea food bhel, fish amritsari & chips, Entrees - Lamb Gustaba, Chicken Basant,  Takka Tak fish, Tandoor - Seekh Kebab, Garlic Naan, Rice and Gulab Jamun Cheese cake.  Everything was amazing.  The meat dishes were flavorful with amazing texture. The fish and chips crispy outside with a moist inside coupled with a great mint chutney.  The seafood bhel - a great twist on a classic with complex flavors - crunchy, sweet, salty, spicy and soft. The Gulab Jamun Cheesecake - 2 desserts in one - light fluffy cheesecake with plump syrupy Gulab Jamun. Both kept there taste and texture separately but together it was sublime.  All the food melts in your mouth and makes your tastebuds sing.  Can’t wait to try the rest of the menu. Will definitely be going back.
